My name is Dhruba Banerjee. I am a first-year MS-HCI student at Carnegie Mellon University.

I am passionate about using technology to create positive social change and improve people's lives. In the past, I have worked on projects related to healthcare, education, and social justice.

I am excited to learn more about human-computer interaction and how to design better user experiences. I am also looking forward to meeting new people and making friends in the HCII community.
